Sacrifice 100 AC for not even enough mana for an extra scorcie when you start at full mana?  This doesn't even make sense to me for soloing purposes.  Anyways, if someone is willing to outline the arguements for the mana schooh of thought for me I'd appreciate it and look forward to hearing your thoughts.<br>
<br>
Jambone Dalewalker<br>
56 Preserver of the Nameless<br>
Moduma Nossum <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukalinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/26/01 12:13:55 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/Kalinn?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC vs. Mana.  Someone argue the other side for me </span><hr size=1> the druid is such a versatile class, that opens up to so many different playstyles.  what every druid needs to do is just WATCH how they themselves play.  ask questions.<br>
 <br>
do i get hit a lot?  <br>
do i run OOM a lot?  <br>
do i play primary healer role often?  <br>
am i a quad kiting soloer?  <br>
what is my role in my guild, my groups and soloing?<br>
<br>
<br>
after you have answered those questions, THEN you determine what your equipment needs are.  soloers or those who find themselves OOM a lot should focus on increasing their mana pool moreso than on ac.  if you play primarily in guild raids, then resists are better for you.  someone who is primary healer and gets hit a lot should take a serious look at their ac.  there is no one way to set up your gear, not when there are so many different ways to play.<br>
<br>
i myself have tried to strike a medium balance, even though i am an ac freak.  self buffed i am at about 870 ac.  one more level and i will have PotG and that will go up to around 900+.  but im also in a transition period right now =)  my wis is at 220, and i desperately need to drop some wis for some resist and ac gear, i just cant figure out WHAT to get rid of without losing massive ac =P <p>-K<br><br>
The right to do something doesn't mean that doing it is right. -William Safire
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujadaepacifica.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jadae Pacifica</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/pacificjade/bunclover.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/26/01 2:04:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AC vs. Mana.  Someone argue the other side for me </span><hr size=1> Being the most diverse class in the game I would advise a fair balance between prime stats and mana/hp pools unless there is a particular task that calls for particular stats/pools to be above average. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urandomuser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>random user</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/26/01 2:37:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The other side</span><hr size=1> I'll argue the other side for you :)<br>
<br>
(Note: this is a hypothetical &quot;I&quot;, and not the real me)<br>
<br>
I primarily play EQ in two ways.  I either group, or I am solo.<br>
<br>
When I solo, I quad-kite.  If I do this right, I never get hit, or at most, get hit just a couple of times.  Having the maximum amount of mana is very important to me, not because I need it for everyday use, but for something goes wrong.  Having enough mana means that I can deal with adds, or having to regroup the quad or whatnot instead of having to zone.  Because I never get hit because I am always sowed and my targets are always snared, the AC isn't that big of a deal.<br>
<br>
Also when I am soloing I like to try and find things I can kill more batches in one sitting.  The reason for this is because I like to kill however many I can, and then just med and go AFK (since I can find a safe spot to med).  Since I don't always get back to the computer right when I hit FM, having more mana means I will have more mana overall.  For example, I can kill two suits in wakening on 1 bar of mana.  Then I go afk for a while and come back and kill 2 more.  If I could only kill one, I couldn't go afk as long, and since I am spending more number of times I go afk, I am being more inefficient (because each time I go afk there is some inefficiency built in).<br>
<br>
The other part of EQ I spend grouped.  I regularly partner with a warrior/monk who both are 2 levels higher than I am.  Also I almost always group with an enchanter.  Thus I never need to pull and rarely have to do crowd control.  I'm good at agro management so I don't get beat on.  Having more mana means that if a big pull comes in and then repops happen for example, I can accelerate my damage output (while still managing agro) so things die quicker so my enchanter doesn't go OOM from crowd control.  If I had less mana, I wouldn't be able to help things die quicker as much, and the enchanter or cleric might get to OOM and then we would have to evac.  Again, I don't get hit a lot because I don't have to pull, and I don't usually have to do crowd control, and I'm good at managing agro.<br>
<br>
<br>
How's that?<br>
<br>
- Xylem, E'ci<br>
<br>
PS.  my actual stats are 914 ac (with PoG and bladecoat or whatever that spell is) and 200 wis. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urandomuser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>random user</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/26/01 2:42:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> grr</span><hr size=1> Grr.  For some reason ezboard crashes me everytime I try to log in.<br>
