<br>
Also..<br>
<br>
High dexterity helps increase the chance of weapon skill raises.<br>
High strength helps increase the chance of offensive skill raises.<br>
<br>
Before level 60 go for WIS, Plus Mana, AC and Plus HP items in that order.<br>
<br>
After level 60 go for AC, Plus Mana, Plus HP and WIS items in that order. That's almost a total reversal with WIS moving from top to last and AC moving from 3rd to last to 1st.<br>
<br>
Only reason for having tons of mana is for AE kiting, but once  you hit level 60 you don't need exp anymore..<br>
<br>
Here's the truth..<br>
<br>
On any major raid you'll realize that by the time a big fight is over you will never be OOM. Druid nukes are just super slow compared to wizards if they even manage to hit a mob to begin with. On the flip side if you choose to heal you will go OOM and heals cannot be resisted. Basically you have two options.<br>
<br>
Cast 5 nukes for like 3K dmg and end up with half a bar of mana or Cast 10 heals for a full 10K and end up OOM.<br>
<br>
Druids get Nature's Touch which is 400 mana and heals 978 dmg. Cleric's get Divine Light which is 350 mana for 910 hp worth of heals.<br>
<br>
